entries.femaleVariant: That went... smoothly.
Might need time to think.
She's probably scared.
Just part of her act.
Prolly needs some time to think. Couple days, tops.
entries.maleVariant: Prolly needs time to think. Couple of days, tops.

entries.femaleVariant: Know what I think? She's scared stiff. She'd have lots to lose if things went sour – everything, in fact.
entries.maleVariant: Y'know what I think? She's scared stiff. She'd have lots to lose if things went sour – everything, in fact.

entries.femaleVariant: Don't worry, she put on an act.
Way back, yeah. Think I just felt lonely.
Yeah, you might be right. I'll call her tomorrow.
So she'll just let things go on as usual?
Augh, she didn't even let me make my point.
She totally blew us off!
Few days down the line, she'll call and tell you her plan to take over Clouds, as if it were her idea.
entries.maleVariant: Few days down the line, she'll call and tell you her plan to take over Clouds, as if it was her idea.

entries.femaleVariant: Needed to show who's boss. We took her by surprise – she couldn't do anything but throw us out.
entries.maleVariant: She needed to show who's boss. We took her by surprise, I mean – she couldn't do anything but throw us out.

entries.femaleVariant: You might be onto something.
She'll call soon enough and ask what we actually wanted.
Why do you ask?
You two have a history?
She was different then. And so was I.
Felt a little tension 'tween you two.
entries.maleVariant: I felt a little tension between you two.

entries.femaleVariant: Tension? Psh. Try straight pissed off.
Really don't understand what tits have to do with sellin' that garbage.
Must work if they do it.
Like everyone in Night City.
W-wait a sec.
What about Woodman?
We kill the motherfucker.
We pay him no mind.
What do you wanna do?
Well, what do you wanna do?
Y'sure he's gonna be there?
entries.maleVariant: You sure he's gonna be there?

entries.femaleVariant: No point bothering about him.
You're right. Let's do it.
Rather not kill him.
Eh... you're right. Hm. Can't let him get off easy.
entries.maleVariant: Heh, yeah. You're right. Can't let him off easy.

entries.femaleVariant: I don't wanna kill him – won't. Sorry, but... ya can't ask that of me.
Ground level? You lettin' Woodman off?
Woodman after all? Even I don't change my mind that quickly.
The fuck you two doing here? Where's Maiko? Why'd she fuckin' call me here?
When Evelyn needed help, you raped her.
I want somebody to unload lead into his face till there is no face.
We'll take the elevator. Quickest way.
I should say so.
Could've also broken her neck – hung up her head like a chandelier till it started to rot.
Why'd you let him go?
Almost felt like the world'd be a better place once he died.
Can't kill in cold blood, won't.
Revenge is rarely worth it.
World has changed.
We got bigger fish to fry.
Self-defense is one thing. You get backed into a corner – you do what nature taught you, survive.
entries.maleVariant: Self-defense is one thing. Get backed into a corner – you do what nature taught ya, survive.

entries.femaleVariant: Woodmans of the world're like mushrooms – always rear their ugly heads from the dirt if conditions're right.
entries.maleVariant: Woodmans of the world're like mushrooms – they always rear their ugly heads from the dirt if the conditions're right.

entries.femaleVariant: Y'know... revenge isn't ever really worth it.
World did change, though.
"Bothering about him"? Who knows how many people he's treated like Evelyn…
You're right... Sorry.
Whole 'nother ball game. Fine, I get it.
You gotta rip 'em outta the ground, root an' all... I guess you're right.
People wanna believe it'll be the miracle pill for their grief, but... that's not how it works.
entries.maleVariant: People wanna believe it'll be the miracle pill for their grief... but that's not how it works.

entries.femaleVariant: All the people he could've hurt – they're all safe now. Think of that.
Let's, uh, let's get out of here, V.
I thought I'd, uh... feel more... I'd be satisfied.
I gotta get back to Maiko with somethin' big.
Appealing to her sense of justice wasn't big enough?
entries.maleVariant: Appealin' to her sense of justice wasn't big enough?

entries.femaleVariant: Maiko only works with specifics.
What now?
Thought you might give up after that.
I'm also partial to specifics.
So – what now?
Gotta think. We need more bodies, that's for sure. I'm gonna talk to the dolls.
I'll call you when I've got something.
See ya later, V. And thanks.
For a minute there, thought you were about call it quits.
V... I go for days tuning virtus in a basement. Know what the chances are of somebody blowin' my head off down there?
Miniscule?
Same as Maiko's empathy. Unlike you, I don't put myself out there.
But this ain't over – not yet.
Can't trust people that see everything as a numbers game.
Line between patting you on the back as their friend, and planting a knife in you as their enemy, is down to a decimal.
I know – right there with you. I... well, used to have a big crush on her. Took me a long time to realize who she really was.
But still... honest or crooked, we need her.
Y'know... I'm also partial to specifics.
Uh-huh, so that's what matters. How many you'll drop, how much ammo you'll use, how many eddies it'll getcha?
Art and dreams of freedom can't be everyone's food.
Sometimes... you gotta deal with the dirt.
You met Maiko. If that prick still works here, it's 'cause he follows her orders pretty damn precisely.
Somebody?
Fine... Want you to do it.
Sure he'll be there?
Don't have an ounce of sympathy for that motherfucker.
So... we goin' there?
Damn straight. Let's end him.
How many more he has lined up…
Just gonna let him get away with that?
Ah-pthu!
Instead, I took her to a ripper. Was due a little something in return.
She should be grateful. And so should you.
Hm, here's my token of gratitude.
Maintenance level.
Ugh. Punch the ground floor. Need to get out of this place.
Sometimes I really don't understand you, V.
And the feeling... it was so fuckin' strong.
They'll never even know they were in danger.
Ehh, but killing in cold blood...
Drop one, someone else'll take his place. Someone worse.
Hey, if it works... Blame the corps all you want, but at the end of the day, says more about us than them.
entries.maleVariant: Hey, if it works... I mean, blame the corps all you want, but at the end of the day, says more about us than them.

entries.femaleVariant: It's like junk food... people don't buy it 'cause they're gonk – they're just poor.
Biz is biz 'n' tits're biz.
Self-defense – that's one thing. But execution? Judy, it's bad karma.
Evelyn needed help, you raped her.
Evelyn's dead.
Evelyn's dead.
Come here just to tell me that? It's fucking kind of you to remember.
Here. Go light a candle.
You know what's worse than a corpo? A wannabe corpo bitch.
You mean Maiko.
Piece o' work, that one. But I'll give her credit – she's dead-on about your chances of pullin' this off.
Can't say no to tits – rest can go fuck itself.
Clearly, you're their target audience.
Second you react with your dick 'stead of your head, you give 'em exactly what they want.
Does it look like I give a shit?
Doesn't matter – they already flushed one down your brain.
Huh, just think, coulda gone divin' this mornin'…
Yeah, you, a deckchair and a Mai Tai with a cocktail umbrella – somehow I don't see it.
A little unwindin'd do you good. Do me good too, actually.
It wouldn'ta been unwindin', not exactly. Got an idea buzzin' in my mind, workin' it, but I can't say if it'll amount to anything.
Nope! Me in a deckchair's me mullin' over coulda, shoulda, wouldas – somethin' I avoid right now.
